1
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,400
It feels so familiar.

2
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,200
I'm back in this place again.

3
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,620
How do you feel?

4
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,400
Are you not feeling well?

5
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:27,160
This place feels very familiar.

6
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,120
The power is out.

7
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,160
Hurry up and take out

8
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,160
the backup light.

9
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,280
You're thinking about

10
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,520
your past with the Prince, right?

11
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,010
It was just an illusion.

12
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,000
It's good that you understand.

13
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,840
Virtual is virtual.

14
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,079
It can never compare to reality.

15
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,480
Is it you again?

16
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,740
Let's find the second Copper Frog first.

17
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,120
I didn't bring it.

18
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:04,640
Didn't I tell you to bring it last night?

19
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,040
When did you say that?

20
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,300
How come I didn't know?

21
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,320
Are the two ears on your head

22
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,520
just for decoration?

23
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,120
No.

24
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,130
Who's there?

25
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,660
(in Thai) Is anyone else here?

26
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,960
We've run into competition.

27
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,240
Did we run into artifact thieves?

28
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,240
Forget it.

29
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,770
Let's find what we came for.

30
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,860
(in Thai) Did they notice?

31
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:18,640
This voice...

32
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,959
why is it so familiar?

33
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,000
Hold them off.

34
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,720
I'll go find the bronze frog.

35
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,860
His voice sounds so familiar.

36
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,700
For the people of both countries.

37
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:39,760
For you.

38
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,560
Apart from the Prince and Princess,

39
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,560
who else can find Buluotuo's Tears?

40
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,450
There must be someone else.

41
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,720
A living person.

42
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:50,760
It's you.

43
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:00,000
Liu Yu, why are you just standing there?

44
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,320
Go find the Bronze Frog.

45
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:01,680
Okay.

46
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,000
Found it.

47
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,520
Give it to me.

48
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:34,200
Aya.

49
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,800
Princess Aya.

50
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,080
Why are you here?

51
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,000
I'm here for the same reason

52
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
that you are.

53
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,960
Why am I here?

54
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:05,880
Who on earth am I?

55
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,240
Aya.

56
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:19,920
Princess.

57
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,000
Princess.

58
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,360
What's wrong?

59
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,400
Who are you?
